Date: Mon, 3 Apr 1995 11:25:33 +0300 (EETDST)
From: Mikko Makela <mmmakela@cc.helsinki.fi>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: speed issues - (fwd)

Forwarded message:
> 	

> 	Hi,
> 		it seems to be faster to use 
> 		shared vars in statements than passing 
> 		args through the parameters 
> 		
> 		I just thought it would be the other way around
> 		thats all really. 
> 			Anyone have any comments?
> 
> 				Brett 

I guess that's because when you use parameters, memory must be reserved
for them and values copied to reserved locations. It's like that in
any language when using "call-by-value"-parameters. Shared variables
mean "call-by-reference"-variables, so no reserving/copying is needed.

-Mikko
