From c9108939@sol.newcastle.edu.auSun Sep  3 22:30:04 1995
Date: Fri, 7 Apr 1995 14:38:43 +1000 (EST)
From: Brett Johansen <c9108939@sol.newcastle.edu.au>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: optimisations - lack of!!!



	hello again ,
		from what I can see Blitz does no optimization at all!!!

	I was amazed to find that constants are not precalculated!!!

		ie.  x = 34 + 67

		produces asm:

			move.l #34,d0
			move.l #67,d1
			add.l d0,d1
			move.l d1,addr x

	34 + 67 should be calculated at run time - I couldn't believe this
	one. I mean leaving them to be calculated by the compiler makes it
	more readable - you can see how you got that value (doesnt happen)
		should be:
			move.l #101,addr x	

		I am writing a shoot'emup game - fairly developed and I 
	have spent ages finding better algorithms etc to make it run fine 
	on a 2000, I use a 1200.  (and succeeded) 
		But now I have started converting the crucial routines
	to asm because by doing my own optimisation I can speed it up 
	at least to twice as fast!!(I was giving blitz more credit before)

	Also there is no reuse of registers - even if the variable is in
		the cpu it is reloaded every time it is needed. :(

		Even so these optimisations can be easily fixed when 
	they get around to it. Maybe thats what they're doing now ?

		But Blitz is still a great language to develop in, no
		questions about that.

				Brett Johansen
---

		current project:  AtomHead (horizontal shootemup) %50


