From relmore@silver.sdsmt.eduSun Sep  3 22:30:04 1995
Date: Sun, 9 Apr 1995 07:36:07 -0600 (MDT)
From: "Richard T. Elmore" <relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Problems receiving Elmore's IncludeLib?


This is a lesson in backing up crucial files:  

I offered the full INCLUDE-library for a small registration fee in BUM7, 
and have had a very good response.  In order to keep up with the number 
of people who registered, I decided to enter all the names and addresses 
into a database program.  Having done this, I begin mailing the 
registered version of the INCLUDE library to those who'd paid for it.  
(Thank all of you!)  

Unfortunately, the database program crashed (a full-blown GURU) during a 
disk-write, and the database file was reduced to zero-bytes (after the 
disk finally validated.)  

I have went through as many envelopes' return-addresses as I could in 
order to reply, but there are many who've registered that I have no way 
to contact as of now.  

This situation causes some serious problems: I don't have any way to 
contact those who've registered except here in a public post, and I don't 
have any way of determining whether those who respond have actually 
registered or not.  

I am left with only one alternative.  I am asking that those of you 
who've registered respond in e-mail and tell me how you'd like the 
Elmore-Include library to be sent to you (e-mail, s-mail address, etc.)  

This would obviously be a chance for people to be dishonest and get the 
Include-library for free, but I guess I have no alternative.  I am just 
asking that those who really *have* paid for the include-library to 
respond, and others out there to resist the urge to tell me you have if 
you really didn't.  I won't be able to tell the difference, but if too 
many dishonest people respond, I won't be able to afford to send copies 
of the library to those who have paid for it.

Please be honest, people!


I deeply apologize for the inconvenience, and to partly compensate for the 
long wait, etc.  I will be offering other registered-shareware for FREE 
along with the INCLUDE-Library.   Thank you!


+-----------------+ 
|Richard T. Elmore|
+-----------------+


