From wlmcgr@netcom.comSun Sep  3 22:30:04 1995
Date: Sun, 9 Apr 1995 15:00:43 -0700 (PDT)
From: "W.L. McGraw" <wlmcgr@netcom.com>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Size of Executables

There have been some discussion on the list about the size of Blitz
executable files. Well the bottom line is that Amiga programmers
can not forever make programs that will run on machines with just
512K of ram. The Mac and PC are running 8 meg and a hard drive for new
software. What we need for the Amiga is a minimum hardware standard that
all users must achieve. For example, 1 meg chip ram, 2 meg total ram,
Kickstart 2.0 and a hard drive would be the minimum hardware standard.
I think this would allow programmers to produce better software.





