From sis3149@sis.port.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:05 1995
Date: Mon, 10 Apr 1995 11:37:30 +0100 (BST)
From: Stephen McNamara <sis3149@sis.port.ac.uk>
To: "Ott M. Aaloe" <OTT@microlnk.ml.ee>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: Size of executable...

On Sun, 9 Apr 1995, Ott M. Aaloe wrote:

> I know there's been discussions about subject but I just though
> perhaps there is some cure for it now...thing that worries me
> is...yes, the size of executable - in my case it's a bit over 400 K 
> and grows all the time (and no, there are no INCBINS)...so I guess 
> A500 users with .5 M ram can forget about my project ;) if the memory 
> is full of program itself...One way to make it smaller is of course 
> try to optimize basic code but that's not enough. As far as I know 
> Blitz includes the whole library if only one command is used from 
> it...so perhaps this can be avoided somehow?  Any ides/suggestions?

I can tell you what I do (e.g. for the debugger, which is hideously big 
anyway).  If I need only one command from a lib (and its not one of my 
libs) then I first try and write it myself (easy in the case of a command 
like CheckAGA - Elmorelib).  If I can't be bothered to rewrite, or 
haven't the time BUT have the source then I'll knick a little code 
(apologies :) ) from the lib and chuck it in a temporary lib of its own.  
This as far as I can tell is the only way to stop the whole library 
growing in size to massive proportions.

Can't imagine what Roketz (I assume you're converting that) must be 
doing if the code is 400k...  BIG program or what (our game is only 400k 
with about 150k of incbined shapes and graphics).

Hey - any one out there got any spare A500s?  Wanna lend us some test 
machines? :)


Steve Mc.

