Hi,
   anyone else noticed this rather lethal bug in Ted?  You know - the bug 
that completely crashes your machine....? :)

   If you haven't then try the following:

	1) Load up TED
	2) Load in a big source file
	3) Move to half way down the file
	4) Now drag the Ted screen to half way down the display
	5) Start dragging out a block
	6) Whilst dragging out the block move the mouse pointer vertically
	  above the Ted screen
	7) Ask yourself why your Amiga suddenly displays a blank screen 
	  locks up completely.

Maybe not everyone has seen/gets this bug - but it seems pretty serious 
to me.  Maybe this bug is only with the latest version of Ted as well?


Steve Mc.

