From sis3147@sis.port.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:05 1995
Date: Mon, 10 Apr 1995 12:03:15 +0100 (BST)
From: Big Will Riker <sis3147@sis.port.ac.uk>
To: blitzlist <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: some pretty weird Blitz bugs..


I was writing a AppIcon program the other day, and it waited
for an event of $800000 or another thing happening..

it was basically..

	Repeat
	  ev.l=WaitEvent
          cx.l=ExchangeMessage
          NPrint Hex$(ev)
        Until ev or cx

Now, imagine my surprise when $800000 was printed but it didnt
exit the repeat until loop.
Sooo, I called up the debugger, and brought up an assembly listing
and I saw that it only compares the lower word of each variable
(and $800000 is in the upper word) if I dont specifically
specify an equality value, so if I had written
	Repeat
	  ev.l=WaitEvent
          cx.l=ExchangeMessage
        Until ev<>0 or cx<>0

it would work.

Anyone else come across this?
Steve.
