From sis3147@sis.port.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:05 1995
Date: Mon, 10 Apr 1995 12:05:22 +0100 (BST)
From: Big Will Riker <sis3147@sis.port.ac.uk>
To: blitzlist <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: Another weird blitz bug


Ok people, try this at home (ask a grown-up to help you)


Function.w a{var.w}
  NPrint var
  Function Return var*2
End Function

Function.w b{var.w}
  NPrint "Oh no! ",var
  Function Return var*10
End Function

main:
c{10}


Before you ask, yes it should be c{10} even though there is no
such function as c{}...

And the ouptut is
Oh no! 10
100

Jeez...talk about stupid eh?


