From D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:05 1995
Date: Mon, 10 Apr 1995 12:53:09 +0100 (BST)
From: Pink <D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.uk>
To: The Blitz list <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: RE: Tan command (Brian)

HI,

  Since I suggested using Sin and Cos to find the Tan function I have 
tested the Tan function at home and had no problems.  Maybe it`s 
something you`re doing:)  I guess you realise that the Tan function 
expects the angle to be in Radians, NOT in degrees.  That means to find 
the Tan of an angle x, and put it in y, you have to do :

y=Tan(x*Pi/180)

  I hope that helped.

