From D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:05 1995
Date: Mon, 10 Apr 1995 13:10:08 +0100 (BST)
From: Pink <D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.uk>
To: The Blitz list <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: RE: Files and array problem

On Sunday 9th April Mike Clark Wrote

> Hi all, got a bit of a problem.
> 
> Files:
> Is there a way a reading a normal file randomly. All I want to do is
> be able to read a normal ascii file from any position in the file, and
> I don't want to do a ReadMem and read the whole file into memory.
> 
  Theres a command called FileSeek with which you can move to any position
in the file.  Look in your Blitz manual for details of how to use it.

> Arrays:
> Is there a way freeing arrays (list or normal) after they have been
> DIMmed, or am I going to have to do an AllocMem?
> 

  There isn`t a specific command to free an array, but arrays can be
re-dimmed.  This means that you could re-dim (Just use the Dim command
again with the same variable name) the array with a size of 0, which
will automatically free the old array, and allocate 0 bytes for the new
array.

> Cheers.
> 

Thats OK.

