From D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:05 1995
Date: Mon, 10 Apr 1995 13:35:44 +0100 (BST)
From: Pink <D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.uk>
To: The Blitz list <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: Finished Proggy

I`ve recently finished a program to generate mazes.  I`ve posted it on 
Aminet under utils/misc/DansMazes1.14.lha as MailWare.  So far in the 
last two weeks I`ve had two mails, both of which claim their kids like 
it, though it could also be used to generate mazes for a game if anyone 
wants to contact me.  It has the following features :

o Creates mazes upto 1000 by 1000 (could be more, but this seems big enough)
o Mazes have only one route through, and all parts of the maze are accesible
o Mazes can be saved in a packed or unpacked format (packed is 1/4 of size!)
o Mazes can be viewed in 2D or 3D
o 2D mazes can be saved as a bitmap
o Configuration via icon information

Thats about it I think.

