Subject: RE: RE: Finished proggy


On Mon, 10 Apr 1995, Steve wrote:

> Can it create mazes such that there is never an empty space
> of 2x2 squares?
> 
> eg. (#=wall)
> ** should never happen
> 
> #############
> # #**# #  # #
> # #**#   ## #
> # ## ### #  #
> # #  # # ####
> #############
> 
> If so, then I think I could use it for my 8 player dungeon
> master type game.. 
> 
> Steve.

Yes, it can! The only restriction at the moment is that the only path through
is from the top to the bottom, with random positions for both.  The algorithm
could be altered so the position at the top is chosen, but it would be VERY
difficult to choose the end position.  I.E.

+-+-+ +-+-+
|   |     |
+ + +-+-+ +
| |       |
+-+-+-+ + +
|     | | |
+ +-+ + + +
|   |   | |
+-+ +-+-+-+

NOTE This was NOT produced using the program, but it IS the type of thing 
to expect, though the mazes are a LOT harder to solve when they get upto 
1000 by 1000:)  One thing to note is the way the mazes are created.  My 
mazes are made by placing walls in between blocks, whereas from your 
diagram it looks as though yours are made by placing completely solid blocks.
If you`re not sure what I mean then download the prog and see, the archive is
only about 45K.


