From gakennedy@cix.compulink.co.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:05 1995
Date: Mon, 10 Apr 95 20:03 BST-1
From: Graham Kennedy <gakennedy@cix.compulink.co.uk>
To: Blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Cc: gakennedy@cix.compulink.co.uk
Subject: Re: Files and arrays problem.

In-Reply-To: <memo.571671@cix.compulink.co.uk>

>>Files:
>>Is there a way a reading a normal file randomly. All I want to do is
>>be able to read a normal ascii file from any position in the file, and
>>I don't want to do a ReadMem and read the whole file into memory.
>Simple fix to this one, you need the command FileSeek, (page 7-6 in the
>manual) Syntax is
>
>    FileSeek filenumber,position
>
>The position is the byte offset from the start of the file.
>you can then use any of the usual input functions (I'd recommend
>something like a$=inkey$(1) to read the file a byte at a time)
>
>
>>Arrays:
>>Is there a way freeing arrays (list or normal) after they have been
>>DIMmed, or am I going to have to do an AllocMem?
>It seems you can do a 'DIM myarray(0)' but not sure if this really
>frees up memory or not.
>
>Hope this helps

Graham K.  


