  Oh, I could run off a list of 10 horrible bugs in Ted, given a little 
time... here's a few...

1) You know how Ted clones the WB screen?  Well, some WB screen sizes 
cause Ted to crash horribly...

2) I don't remember exactly how this one works, but you can cause crashes 
by playing with the menus as you're selecting a block of text...

3) That copperlist in the menu bar really makes the display look hideous 
if you drag the screen up and down, with other screens in front...

4) The filerequester moves to a garbage path if you click too quickly 
(like just as the first entry is appearing)... 

5) why does the entire screen have to update almost any time you do 
anything with a block of text marked?

I could go on and on, but the point is that Ted is dragging Blitz down... 
it makes a powerful language look like a hack... Someone's got to rewrite 
it...

