From acid@iconz.co.nzSun Sep  3 22:30:06 1995
Date: Mon, 17 Apr 1995 16:58:25 +1200 (NZST)
From: Simon or Mark <acid@iconz.co.nz>
To: "Pedro J. Cervantes Pintor" <mfc@xanum.uam.mx>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: pointers (again)



On Sat, 15 Apr 1995, Pedro J. Cervantes Pintor wrote:

>   Does somebody knows how to handle strings inside pointers ?
>   
>   NEWTYPE.Thing
>     string1$
>     *next_item.Thing
>   END NEWTYPE
>   
>   *item1.Thing
>   *item1\string1="HELLO !!"                ;i can do this
>                                           
>                                           
>  
>   *item1.Thing
>   *item1=Allocmem_ (Sizeof.Thing,0)
>   *item1\string1="HELLO"                   ;I CAN'T do this (in a statement)
>

You might want to try:

*item1=Allocmem_(Sizeof.Thing,65536)

As this will zero out the allocated memory - otherwise, Blitz thinks a 
string already exists!


