From relmore@silver.sdsmt.eduSun Sep  3 22:30:06 1995
Date: Sun, 23 Apr 1995 18:43:25 -0600 (MDT)
From: "Richard T. Elmore" <relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu>
To: Brian Skreeg <oz@ozzy.demon.co.uk>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: Quick variables etc, 

On Sun, 23 Apr 1995, Brian Skreeg wrote:

> 	When using quick variables do I need to .q on the end of the variable
> every time it's used or just the once at the start?

The first time you declare a variables' type it is assumed to be that 
type from then on in your source.  

> 	Also is there a way to speed up If thens? Possibly using CMP commands
> or something ASMy like that?

*POSSIBLY* though it would probably be easier to optimize the way you 
compare things in BASIC first...  If you'll send me a code-segment 
containing your slow IF-THENs, I'll see if there is a way to optimize 
them without resorting to ASM... (If you do go the ASM route, you'd 
really better know what you're doing in both ASM and Blitz.)

Comment the code segment if you can so I can see what your intended 
results should be.

	+---------------------------------------------------------------+
	|      Richard T. Elmore   -   "Head" of HeadSoft Software      |
	| E-MAIL: relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu          TEL: (605) 348-3337 |     
