From sis3149@sis.port.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:07 1995
Date: Mon, 24 Apr 1995 12:27:56 +0100 (BST)
From: Stephen McNamara <sis3149@sis.port.ac.uk>
To: "Pedro J. Cervantes Pintor" <mfc@xanum.uam.mx>
Cc: Blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: anim files

On Sun, 23 Apr 1995, Pedro J. Cervantes Pintor wrote:

>   Where can i find information about the formats not suported 
> from Blitz for "anim" files ....

The standard blitz can lay anim5 file and load in animbrushes as shapes.

If you use our anim library (RIAnimLib) you can play back Anim5 & Anim7 
(short and long types). Our library also supports different palettes for 
each frame.


Steve Mc.

