> orily. Here's an example of what I mean :-
> 
> Dim *strngs.s(1000) ; set up 1000 strings
> *strng(0)="Message Number 1"
> *strng(1)="abcdefg..."
>    .
> mystruct\msg=&*strng(0)  ; \msg is a.l, assigns address of string to msg
> Print Peek.s(mystruct\msg)  ; to print the message text
> 
> I hope that's of some help to you cos I spent ages trying to sort out
> why my strings didn't work within statements.
