    - My version of Blitz Basic2 is 1.7.  I have been trying to use the
      examples/blitzmode/dbscrolling.bb2 example to understand how to do
      map block scrolling.  I was disturbed to notice that when 
      running this example on my Amiga 2000 or my brother's 1200 that 
      blocks which scrolled into view tended to blink/flicker especially 
      when the joystick was moved quickly to change directions.

      Not all blocks would blink.  Perhaps just a few.  They would continue
      to flicker even when scrolling is completely stopped.
      With the dbscrolling example, I can get this to happen consistently
      if I first move the joystick to the left. 

      Is this a problem with the example or with Blitz?


    - Using the dbscrolling example as a base, I tried to write a 
      horizontal/vertical scroll map block routine with a full screen 
      slice using 32 colour bitmaps.  I don't need to scroll diagonally.
      Blocks really tend to blink/flicker now and I also can't get the
      scroll routine to work yet (wrong blocks appearing).

      Does anyone have a horizontal/vertical block scroll algorithum or
      sample code they can share with me?

 
