		This is a problem with the example most likely.
		When you move to fast, or change direction the blocks either
	didn't get blitted to both bitmaps(so one is blank- and flicks),
	 or hadn't been blited in time before the next vblank <- unlikely
> 
> 
>     - Using the dbscrolling example as a base, I tried to write a 
>       horizontal/vertical scroll map block routine with a full screen 
>       slice using 32 colour bitmaps.  I don't need to scroll diagonally.
>       Blocks really tend to blink/flicker now and I also can't get the
>       scroll routine to work yet (wrong blocks appearing).
