From sis3149@sis.port.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:07 1995
Date: Thu, 27 Apr 1995 08:50:31 +0100 (BST)
From: Stephen McNamara <sis3149@sis.port.ac.uk>
To: Brett Johansen <c9108939@sol.newcastle.edu.au>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: crunch mania - 

On Thu, 27 Apr 1995, Brett Johansen wrote:

> 	I received some advice to use crunch mania in my game!
> 
> 		Can you give me an example of the commands
> 	required., to acheive a result.

Right, first off get onto AMinet and find the crunch mania program.  Then 
find someone with the user library that uncrunches crunch mania data files 
(not sure who's lib it is).  The only command you actually need to unpack 
the data files is

	crmdecrunch source[,dest]

(I think thats the command name)
If you don't provide a destination, the data is unpacked over itself.

So to load your map files, do something like:

	Bload <Myfile>,0
	CRMDecrunch start(0),&myarray(0,0)

That should happily sort the data out for you.

> 	Also how about the sprite question I asked,
> 		nobody helped me.
> 
> 	HOw do I do sprite priority on dual playfield with the display lib???

to set the sprite priorities you'll have to directly set the hardware 
registers yourself.  There are no commands inside the library name 
SpritePriority.  I suggest you either get the Hardware REference Manual 
and find out what the bits are you need to set (I think they are in 
BPLCON1 or 2).

I think there might be a displaylib command though that you can use to 
actually change the value of BPLCONx inside the coplist object. Make sure 
that you OR your new value over the value that is already there since it 
almost certainly has other setup information inside the register.


Steve Mc.

+---------------------------------------------------------------------------+
                 L E A D I N G   E D G E   S O F T W A R E
+---------------------------------------------------------------------------+
                Hang                 | Current project :                    +
   sis3149@sisvax.sis.port.ac.uk     | [::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::] +
+---------------------------------------------------------------------------+



