From ngh94@aber.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:07 1995
Date: Thu, 27 Apr 1995 13:56:15 +0100
From: NIGEL HUGHES <ngh94@aber.ac.uk>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: Level maps.. 

In message <19529.9504271114@delta.ahl.co.uk>, 
	Colin Saunders <colin@abstract-hardware-ltd.co.uk> writes:
> 
> Dear All,
> 
> Speculative question as I haven't tried this yet...
> 
> Is it possible to load in the level block maps from file using, say,
> readmem_ and then to access this as an array?
> 
>     Thanks,
> 
>         Colin.
> 
> 

Colin,
	Yup, do something like

	Dim My_Array.b(9,9)
	
	if WriteFile(0,"ram:test")
		writemem 0,&My_Array,10*10
		closefile 0
	endif

	if readfile(0,"ram:test")
		readmem 0,&My_Array,10*10
		closefile 0
	endif

That works fine, I use it for some of my stuff.


	Nigel Hughes


