On Thu, 27 Apr 1995, Maestria en Filosofia wrote:

>   And one more problem...
>   I live in America (Mexico :) ) so i use NTSC SO i have problems with 
> MED songs, they play faster and the med library (blitz) doesn't have any 
> command to make them play slower. I thougt to use the MED and OctaMED 
> libraries (Teijo Kinuen) but i don't know how to install and use this 
> from blitz. Does anybody knows what should i do? :)

  You need to set up an interrupt to handle the MED songs... like so...

 SetInt5
  If si>-1
   si+1
   If si>4 Then si=0 Else PlayMed
  EndIf
 End SetInt


  That should do the trick for NTSC... 

