From relmore@silver.sdsmt.eduSun Sep  3 22:30:08 1995
Date: Fri, 28 Apr 1995 06:57:16 -0600 (MDT)
From: "Richard T. Elmore" <relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu>
To: MACIEJ GORNY <GORN4907@mars.rowan.edu>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: Q: how to recover WB's palette

On Thu, 27 Apr 1995, MACIEJ GORNY wrote:

> Date: Thu, 27 Apr 1995 12:28:37 EST
> From: MACIEJ GORNY <GORN4907@mars.rowan.edu>
> To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
> Subject: Re: Q: how to recover WB's palette
> 
> >    The current prefs files are in Ram:ENV/ somewhere (possibly 
> > ENV:sys/pallete.prefs)  and are, from what I gather .iff files. 
> > 
> I tried reading palette.prefs with LoadPalette command but it says it 
> can't find CMAP (color map I assume), so it can't be pure IFF file.
> 
> maciej 

The palette.prefs file for 2.x is more-or-less an IFF-ILBM containing a 
palette, but since 3.0 the standard has been changed to a new IFF type called 
FORM PREF.  I know how to parse both these types, as well as 1.3 
system-configuration files to derive the palette prefs you're looking for. 
(Most of the info is in the RKMs.)


