From josh@pinsight.comSun Sep  3 22:30:08 1995
Date: Fri, 28 Apr 1995 12:20:45 -0700 (PDT)
From: Josh Farley <josh@pinsight.com>
To: Jamie Burns <jay@burns.demon.co.uk>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: Screen Tags?



On Fri, 28 Apr 1995, Jamie Burns wrote:

>  Does anybody know how to get rid of the title bar from an intuition screen?

  Yes.

>   Ive tried playing with the screen tags but cant seem to find the right bit to
>  switch it off..

  Oh, you want me to tell you??? :)

  Use the following Tags:

#SA_Quiet     , True
#SA_ShowTitle , False

  Also use a MenusOff command after opening a window...

>   Also, on the subject of screen tags, does anybody know how to open a proper
>  OS3+ looking screen (ie. a nice black trim under the white title bar) ??

  Use the #SA_LikeWorkbench , True tag... it should help...

>   And one last thing..  I heard there was some cool AMIGA mode hardware
>  scrolling stuff around here, dont suppose someone could mail me some?

First use this code after opening your screen:

 *s0.Screen=Peek.l(Addr Screen(0))
 *v0.ViewPort=*s0\_ViewPort
 *r0.RasInfo=*v0\RasInfo

Now, use the following code in your main loop:

 *r0\_BitMap=Addr BitMap(cb),x,y
 ScrollVPort_ *v0
 cb=1-cb

Where cb= the current bitmap number (for double buffering)
      x = the x offset within that bitmap
      y = the y offset within that bitmap

This should work beautifully...

Josh Farley     Netmail: 1:119/88     E-Mail: josh@pinsight.com
