From mfc@xanum.uam.mxSun Sep  3 22:30:08 1995
Date: Mon, 1 May 1995 23:18:02 -0500 (CDT)
From: "Pedro J. Cervantes Pintor" <mfc@xanum.uam.mx>
To: MACIEJ GORNY <GORN4907@mars.rowan.edu>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: Q: Using AvailMem_



On Mon, 1 May 1995, MACIEJ GORNY wrote:

> Does anybody know what are the parameters that AvailMem_ needs to 
> show the available memory? is there anyway to check seperately how 
> much fast and how much chip RAM is left?
> 
> Thanks!
> 
   Maciej :

  The function "availMem" only need the "attributes" parameter
  
  so from Blitz you'll have to do...:
    size=AvailMem_ (attributes)
    
  ..from assembler ....:
    D1 = attributes
    D0 = Size
    
  ...AND the attributes are !! ....:     :)
  
   #MEMF_ANY      = 0
   #MEMF_PUBLIC   = 1 ASL 0
   #MEMF_CHIP     = 1 ASL 1
   #MEMF_FAST     = 1 ASL 2
   #MEMF_LOCAL    = 1 ASL 8
   #MEMF_24BITDMA = 1 ASL 9
   #MEMF_CLEAR    = 1 ASL 16
   #MEMF_LARGEST  = 1 ASL 17
   #MEMF_REVERSE  = 1 ASL 18
   #MEMF_TOTAL    = 1 ASL 19  
   #MEMF_BLOCKSIZE= 8
   #MEMF_BLOCKMASK= #MEMF_BLOCKSIZE-1
   
  
  examples :
    size=AvailMem_ (#MEMF_CHIP)     ;free chip mem
    
    size=AvailMem_ (#MEMF_FAST | #MEMF_LARGEST) ;largest block of free 
fastRAM
    
 
  by the way ... this are the same attributes for the "AllocMem_" function
  
                  
  good luck ..GREETINGS !!
  
  Pedro C.
  


