From relmore@silver.sdsmt.eduSun Sep  3 22:30:08 1995
Date: Wed, 3 May 1995 07:32:06 -0600 (MDT)
From: "Richard T. Elmore" <relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu>
To: Vaughan Roberts <vroberts@yoyo.cc.monash.edu.au>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: GTButtons

On Wed, 19 Apr 1995, Vaughan Roberts wrote:

> 	I hope someone out here can help, I want to mark a GTbutton as
> disabled.  I have no worries turning it off (GTDisable), but what I 
> want to do is shade it in so people don't click on it.

After the GTDisable command, use the Redraw command from the old gadgets 
library...  The image is SHOULD to redraw itself and display the mesh 
you're looking for automatically, but since it doesn't, forcing it to 
re-render will do the trick.


> B.T.W. Is it possible to add a bar item (i.e. ~~~~~~) to my menus?

As long as you're using Blitz's menu system, you can't add a "real" bar 
item.  That is a property of GadTools menus.  I've seen a lot of people 
"fake" it with disabled menuitems containing dashes, etc. but they never 
look like the baritems of GadTools.  

I'm thinking about writing a library to handle GTMenus soon, but for now, 
I guess faking it with Blitz's Menu commands is all you can hope for.


 
