 Simon:

 
  After several tests, i found that the problem 
is in the "inicube" statement. Here is my program:
 
Newtype.point
  x.w
  y.w
  z.w
End Newtype
 
Newtype.cube
  c.point[8]
End Newtype
 
original.cube\c[1]\x=0
 
Statement inicube {}
  SHARED original.cube
  original\c[1]\x=0,0,0
  original\c[2]\x=1,0,0
  original\c[3]\x=1,1,0
  original\c[4]\x=0,1,0
  original\c[5]\x=0,0,1
  original\c[6]\x=1,0,1
  original\c[7]\x=1,1,1
  original\c[8]\x=0,1,1
End Statement               
 
inicube {}
 
;*********************************************************
 
when i run this, i get the "Software error - task held ...." 
without any Blitz error message. The Guru number is: 
00000003.0000DE30
 
I tested this program in Blitz Basic 2 V1.7 ; the runtime 
error debugger was activated with autorun and interrupt 
checking; and  without any aditional libraries. My computer 
is an Amiga 500, 1MbChip, 1 drive, OS 1.3
 
      
 maybe it's a Pedro's bug rather than a Blitz bug (i hope)
 
  Pedro C.


