From J.A.R.Marshall@exeter.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:09 1995
Date: Fri, 5 May 1995 12:39:36 +0300
From: J.A.R.Marshall@exeter.ac.uk
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Serial File Input Bug. Crash with Runtime Errors on

Just a quick note to say that I`ve had some problems using
Edit$ to input serial files into variables. The problem seemed
to be something to do with trying to load strings into an array
inside a NewType, but into an element outside those dimensioned
in the NewType definition (still with me?). To make things stranger
the bug vanished when the length of the string to be input with Edit$
was changed, (not necessarily down, just some values didn`t work).
BUT, THE WORST PART WAS...
the runtime error debugger didn`t catch the problem, but caused a
software failure. When my Last Alert proggy came up after the crash,
it seemed that the Blitz2 code had tried to access an illegal (ie. odd)
address! I was using Blitz 1.7 (I think), anyway the update supplied on
BUM 6. I`ve got the problem sorted now, by tidying up my code, but I still
don`t think that it should have bummed out like that, just trying to
access a non-existant array element... hmmmmm.

	just thought everyone might like to no, hope you`re paying
	attention Simon and Mark!
	
	Jim \:)

PS. Someone please tell me the email address for Simon and Mark, so I can
report stuff like this direct...
	
-- 
