From mfc@xanum.uam.mxSun Sep  3 22:30:09 1995
Date: Fri, 5 May 1995 19:35:41 -0500 (CDT)
From: "Pedro J. Cervantes Pintor" <mfc@xanum.uam.mx>
To: Simon or Mark <acid@iconz.co.nz>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: 3d cube



On Fri, 5 May 1995, Simon or Mark wrote:

> Are you having any luck with that cube drawing program. As far as
> "I'm" concernced if there is a bug in blitz that makes your program crash 
> with runtime errors on I need to know about it.
> 
 Simon:

 
finally my program it's running; i just add an "Extra.w" 
variable in the Newtype.cube definition
 
     Newtype.cube
       c.point[8]
       extra.w
     End Newtype 
     
 
and that's it..
   ..GREETINGS !!!

  by the way, in future releases i would like to see things like this:

   Function.MyOwnType WOW {}
   .
   .
   End Function
   

Thing1.MyOwnType=.....

  thing2.MyOwnType=Thing1     etc,etc


