First I am wondering wether I am the first person to use the Includes (I
got them from BB2 Distribution in Colognia) or the only one having
buggy system includes...

It all started with my program (converting some C includes for TRITON
(a very good GUI Enhancer!!) that I needed the system includes for it.

*BUT* using 'XINCLUDE' seems to work within one (same!) file, but it
doesn't work with several files, like in the system includes.

I xincluded e.g. "exec/types.bb2"
this file xincluded "exec/nodes.bb2" and "exec/lists.bb2"
these files xincluded *both* "exec/types.bb2" again. Result: Error.
I found it out compiling these files after having removed the xinclude
lines...

So, what does this %/&(!-xinclude command exists, when it doesn't
work right??


And: There are some bugs in the includes ... Keywords enclosed by
other letters so that the compiler doesn't recognize them ...

