Hullo there mfc@xanum.uam.mx,

On 6 May 95 you murmered to All about the gothic subject of '3d cube', and I
was just thinking...

 > when i run this, i get the "Software error - task held ...."
 > without any Blitz error message. The Guru number is:
 > 00000003.0000DE30
 > 
 > I tested this program in Blitz Basic 2 V1.7 ; the runtime
 > error debugger was activated with autorun and interrupt
 > checking; and  without any aditional libraries. My computer
 > is an Amiga 500, 1MbChip, 1 drive, OS 1.3

That guru is an address error. Its caused by attempting to read or write a word
or longword that is at an uneven address. It only occurs on 68000 or 68010, so
it might not be Blitz or your code.

Catch you on the dark side...

James  founder of GOTHSOFT DEVELOPMENTS  and  ////\oo/\\\\ net.goth


