From cca93057@sun1.bham.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:10 1995
Date: Tue, 9 May 1995 09:17:26 +0100
From: MO Tiffany <cca93057@sun1.bham.ac.uk>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: wbwidth & wbheight


> 	I,ve just run into a weird problem concerning wbwidth & wbheight. For
> some reason they are suddenly returning the wrong sizes for my workbench 
> screens for example my wbench is set for 676 width and 467 height and WBwidth
> returns 640 &WBheight returns 400. I haven't ever had any sort of problem 
> with these commmands  before so I'm trying to figure out how to rectify 
> the situation. I am using V1.9 on an a4000/040 plus I recently used Moned3
> to change the position of my DBLntsc Screens so they are centered properly. 
> I'm not sure if this could be the problem so if any of you GURU's know the
> deal I'd be greatful for any help.

I bumped into this one some time ago , its quite easy to get round, but because
by Amigas dead at the mo, i cant give you any exact code...
BUT - I`ll try and do it off the top of my head.

NB: full newtypes are in amigalibs.res, or can be convertted from the RKMs
    You need .Screen

function.w WBW
  WBToScreen 0
  *s.Screen=peek.l(addr Screen (0))
  function return *s\width
end function

and replace width with height for WBH.  Thats something like it, but as i said, i cant say for sure, or even that this code is good (havent touched Blitz for about 6 weeks now!)

Mark Tiffany / SgtBilko
