> 	My graphics artist is drawing the map tiles for our 
> 		side-on-shootemup. We have struck a few problems!
> 
> 	PROBLEM 1:
> 		The RI map editor (I think that is it - sorry guys :-))
> 	only works on the 1200 and my graphics man only has a 2000!

Get the latest version from Aminet as LESMapEditorV2 (or something).  
It much more stable and shouldn't fall down badly on pre OS3.0.

> 	PROBLEM 2:
> 		Does anybody know of a map editor that allows you to
> 		edit the tiles and place them all in the one package.

The latest map editor has an ARexx port with a large instruction base.  
It doesn't support editing itself, but once ShapeZ II has be upgraded 
(Nigel? :) ) to have an ARexx port both programs will be set up to 
communicate together and swap shapes - meaning that you'll be able to 
import/export between the programs.



Steve Mc.

