From acid@iconz.co.nzSun Sep  3 22:30:10 1995
Date: Wed, 10 May 1995 22:50:43 +1200 (NZST)
From: Simon or Mark <acid@iconz.co.nz>
To: blitz list <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: What the hell is happening at Acid


Hmmm,

Well we had to cancel the ABC cover disk for Amiga Format.

We have printed the new manuals, and I am finding my one very
good all though I fogot the bb2 object listings which I miss...

I (Simon) have just finished a major program for Television which
involves zooming through the body and playing games in different organs. 
This has taken some 3 months of my time.

Acid Software is very much in overdraft, I would say how much but our New 
Zealand dollar is doing some very stupid things grrrrr

We will be having cash injected when both the TV company pays for the 
work I have done and we do a deal with CodeMasters for publishing rights 
to Skid Sega which is coming along very nicely.

BUM8 is coming, over 1500 people world wide are majorly pissed off with 
me and Icannot go on with out appeasing these bad vibes which arrive 
daily in the mailbox, via the phone, through the net and occasioanally 
the odd drunk down at the pub...

BUM8 will not include a new editor, it will include some Acid libraries 
and a section of the new manual with the rest of it available to you our 
humble users at cost plus nz%.

The new manual IS ringbound, and Giles our UK manager will be happy to 
print sections for those wanting to offer printed documentation to their 
libraries.

Blitz, the Jaguar and Andrew's Amiga are now connected and doing well. We 
have some 400 polygons in half a frame and we think the Jaguar is well 
quite a suitable graphics adaptor for an Amiga, quite frankly I do not 
see how C= can come out with a chipset that is better or cheaper.

So what does this all mean? Yes ABC will be ready for release when Escom 
rolls out the Amiga again. I advise all Blitz users to get off their buts 
and get some demo's together so we can really push it and help make the 
Amiga a success once again. I can count the number of programs written in 
Blitz that I think do it justice one two hands. I hope there is a lot 
going down that I don't know about...

As for Mark, he is still as gloomy a flatmate as one could want... He IS 
going to get his own internet account so I can reclaim my electronic 
responsibility. Actually our discussions regarding networking are kind of 
exciting and of course his help with getting our Jaguar/Sega support for 
Blitz going has been invaluable.

Anyway, I AM sorry about the lack of support and not replying to things I 
should have. Depending on how the money flows I'd say there's a good 
possibility Acid could be the great company you all think it should be. 
However We do have to pay the bills so I'll blame it all on the hardware 
and it's manufaturers, shush, typical software company...

Simon

p.s. can someone please post this on blitz-ami

p.p.s. wasn't the X-Files good tonight?




