From relmore@silver.sdsmt.eduSun Sep  3 22:30:10 1995
Date: Wed, 10 May 1995 06:40:50 -0600 (MDT)
From: "Richard T. Elmore" <relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu>
To: MACIEJ GORNY <GORN4907@mars.rowan.edu>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: Q: Blank 'System Request' under 1.3 with .exe files


On Tue, 9 May 1995, MACIEJ GORNY wrote:

> I have a weird problem. When i created an executable and then tried 
> to run it from Workbench, I get this strange looking system requester 
> window: no message, even buttons do not have letters on them. The 
> whole requester window is blank, only buttons' outlines are visible.


It sounds to me like you left "runtime errors" enabled when you compiled 
your program.  Since BUM7 at least, if you leave runtime errors enabled 
in an executeable you create, be sure there is an "END" statement at the 
end of your program, or this requester will appear.


