From D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:10 1995
Date: Wed, 10 May 1995 13:50:21 +0100 (BST)
From: Pink <D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.uk>
To: The Blitz list <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: RE: RE: 3d Cube

On Fri, 5 May 1995, Pedro J. Cervantes Pintor wrote:

> 
> 
> On Fri, 5 May 1995, Simon or Mark wrote:
> 
> > Are you having any luck with that cube drawing program. As far as
> > "I'm" concernced if there is a bug in blitz that makes your program crash 
> > with runtime errors on I need to know about it.
> > 
>  Simon:
> 
>  
> finally my program it's running; i just add an "Extra.w" 
> variable in the Newtype.cube definition
>  
>      Newtype.cube
>        c.point[8]
>        extra.w
>      End Newtype 
>      
This is a bit of a hack.  The reason that the program crashed is that the 
range of the index should be from 0 to 7, NOT from 1 to 8.  The version 
of Blitz in Bum7 now checks this range if run time errors are enabled, so 
I guess you`re using an older version.  I`m suprised Simon or Mark didn`t 
notice this problem :)

>  
> and that's it..
>    ..GREETINGS !!!
> 
>   by the way, in future releases i would like to see things like this:
> 
>    Function.MyOwnType WOW {}
>    .
>    .
>    End Function
>    
> 
> Thing1.MyOwnType=.....
> 
>   thing2.MyOwnType=Thing1     etc,etc
> 
> 
> 
I agree totally.  It would also be nice to be able to do a Dim in a 
Function or a Statement.  Either to redim a SHARED variable and/or to Dim 
a temporary variable for use within the Function/Statement.


