  routine, and then things really get off topic!  What's the relationship
  between a horizontal scroll and sex?  Don't answer that!

  While I'm here, I do have one more question.  Game programming is quit new
  to me (thats why I'm still having problems with the scroll routine). I have
  however written many business applications in other languages; thus 
  programming/problem solving is not new to me.  My question is this:

    Should one be able to write a commercial quality game in Blitz Basic
    without having to resort to writing your own assembler routines or using
    "advanced" techniques (such as cludges, etc. which seem to come up from
    time to time in blitz-list conversations)??

    Or if I just stick to standard blitz commands (with no to little 
    assembler) am I just wasting my time?  Maybe many of you are advanced
    programmers pushing your ideas to the limits, but it seem you guys 
    (and gals) go through a hell of a lot at times to get things to work
    with Blitz. 

   
