Just recently Pedro J. Cervantes Pintor wrote:

>   ..But in Blitz 2 User Guide says that the Arrays hold n+1 elements 
> (  a(50) holds 0..50 inclusive ), so what happen ...
 
I think you`re confusing the two different types of arrays.

Theres the   Dim (n)   whose index ranges from 0 to n, and theres
NEWTYPE .foo
  bar.w[n]
End NEWTYPE

which ranges from 0 to n-1.  The reference in the Blitz 2 User Guide is 
probably refering to the  Dim  type.

