Subject: Screen Bitmaps


I`v had a bit of trouble recently with the ShowBitmap command as I found 
it difficult to create a bitmap the same size as the one used by the 
screen.  Apparently the screen uses a bitmap slightly wider than the 
actual displayed width.  I found this out by using the ScreensBitmap 
command and looking at the bitmap newtype from within the excellent LES 
debugger, and if I create a bitmap using the XClip field as the width 
then all problems are solved.

Two questions really:
Does anyone know why this is?
  and
Is there anyway to know this size in advance without actually creating 
the screen, getting the ScreensBitmap and then Peek ing the XClip value?

