From relmore@silver.sdsmt.eduSun Sep  3 22:30:11 1995
Date: Fri, 12 May 1995 12:26:01 -0600 (MDT)
From: "Richard T. Elmore" <relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu>
To: Pink <D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.uk>
Cc: The Blitz list <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: RE: Gadtools Menus

On Fri, 12 May 1995, Pink wrote:

> Recently Steve McNamara announced that he had written a library to use 
> the Gadtools menus.  Just a little question, are these any different from 
> setting the new look menus flag for the menu owning window?  If I do this 
> on my 3.0 Amiga 1200 the menus created look exactly the same as the 
> Workbench menus, unless I`m mistaken:)

Besides being automatically font-sensitive, GTMenus have the added 
advantage of allowing a REAL separator-bar... (No more kludging it with 
a string of ~~~~~~~~.)  

The biggest advantage has got to be the font/screen sensitivity though, 
try to make a menu with Blitz's menu commands that will look right (even 
with checkmarks and shortcut keys) under fonts from 8 to 24 points.... 
Not very easy to do!

