Ive just put a nice ListView gadget into my current program, with " Add "  "Delete" buttons positioned underneath.

Everthing went well until i came to put in the 'Delete' code.  I realised that when you clicked on a ListView gadget the item under the mouse is highlight then un-highlighted when you press and release the mouse button.  

Is it possible for the item to remain highlighted until the user selects another item or clicks again?  This means you can see exactly what item you
are deleting.


~Paul~


From ronaldo@duncan.xs4all.nlSun Sep  3 22:30:11 1995
Date: 15 May 95 20:41:48 -0100
From: Ronald Kuiper <ronaldo@duncan.xs4all.nl>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Arexx


Hello Josh!

On 13 May 95 you wrote:

 > Does anyone have some code for adding an Arexx port to a Blitz
 > program? I've played with it some, but have had little success...

Maybe this will help:

#RXCOMM=$1000000
#RXFF_RESULT=$20000
#RXFF_STRING=$40000

Macro send
SendRexxCommand msgptr,cmd$,#RXCOMM|#RXFF_STRING|#RXFF_RESULT
End Macro

Macro back
Repeat
 rmsg.l=RexxEvent(port)
 If IsRexxMsg(rmsg)
 If GetRexxResult(rmsg,2) > 256
 ant$=GetResultString(rmsg)
 EndIf
 EndIf
Until IsRexxMsg(rmsg)
End Macro

port.l=CreateMsgPort("POORT")
msgptr.l=CreateRexxMsg(port,"","ADPro")

cmd$="OPTIONS RESULTS;VERSION;EXIT ADPRO_RESULT"
!send:!back
NPrint ant$
MouseWait
End

This program should print the version of Adpro...


       _
      /_)
Grtz / \onald.


