Subject: Re: Blitz with ProTracker (fwd)



>>Not too long ago, tom wrote:

>> How can I get blitz to play a sound module properly.  I friend gave me
>> a sample ProTracker module to use in a demo I am writing for him.
>> Using AMFC Pro I converted it to a SoundTracker and NoiseTracker mod;
>> One of the three modules would not play at all (can't remember which now -
>> perhaps SoundTracker).  The other two played at far to slow a rate and 
>> then > hung my machine.
>> 
>> Any Ideas?

>Easy way: use CIATrackerlib from Neil (Attachment to this Mail).
>Problem: you must fix it for every processor (look in the manuals).

>Other way: convert it to MED and use the MED-commands. But: the MED-lib
>in Blitz can't handle default speed! you must "set" them in a way like:
>(But IMHO MED is the best way to make proper replay in a demo)

>.Interrupt5:
>PlayMED
>PlayMED
>...
>Return


Andrew,

Thanks for your suggestions.  I have considered using CIATrackerLib, but 
I would prefer not to have to tinker with accommodating each processor
(if I can help it).

Converting to MED may be an option (providing I can find a utility to do 
this).

I'm going on memory here (mine not the computer's), but was there not a
library, converted from AMOS which could play mods properly.  I believe 
it was by a Paul Reece?


Thanks again

Tom


