From D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:12 1995
Date: Wed, 17 May 1995 15:06:40 +0100 (BST)
From: Pink <D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.uk>
To: The Blitz list <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: Guru during compilation

I`ve just recently found a strange bug during compilation (NOT 
execution).  It only needs one line to test :

S$=GetProgName{}

When this above line is compiled (even if just trying to make an 
executeable) it gurus with #80000004 (Illegal instruction).  Also if you 
try :

S.w=GetProgName{}

it doesn`t actually guru, but if run time errors are enabled it also 
brings up a run time error.


Bit strange really, all I was trying to do was make a function called 
GetProgName{} :)

