From acid@iconz.co.nzSun Sep  3 22:30:12 1995
Date: Thu, 18 May 1995 10:52:38 +1200 (NZST)
From: Simon <acid@iconz.co.nz>
To: Joe Bott <zor@execpc.com>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: BitplanesBitmap



On Wed, 17 May 1995, Joe Bott wrote:

> Hello! I know this has been explained several times, but how does one 
> effectivly use the BitplanesBitmap command? I'm trying to figure out how 
> to blit my 1 bitplane image on a 3-4 bitplane bitmap, and get something 
> beside only color #1...
> 
> Thanks
> Joe
>
That is not what it is for, use the "excess color" optional parameter in 
the blit command to blit a 1 color shape in different colors. Hmmm, well 
you can use bitplanesbitmap for speed but unless you are blitting to a 
clean area of the bitmap you will get color-mixing, which is good for 
somethings but not good for others. 
 > 
> 
> 


