From relmore@silver.sdsmt.eduSun Sep  3 22:30:13 1995
Date: Thu, 18 May 1995 15:42:45 -0600 (MDT)
From: "Richard T. Elmore" <relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu>
To: Ralph Barbagallo <rbarbaga@cs.uml.edu>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: Random Number Routine

On Thu, 18 May 1995, Ralph Barbagallo wrote:

> 	Does anyone have a good random number routine?  I've been messing 
> around with VPOS, but I can't get a good one.  It seems to always come
> up with the same number since the beam is at roughly the same position when the
> game starts.  

If you haven't already got it, I believe BUM5 or BUM6 had my RRandomize 
and RRnd functions that should do what you want... The same set of 
libraries also had a "Ticks" function that is similar to "Timer" in other 
BASICs, so if you do:

RRandomize Ticks
Number=RRNd(1,10)

You won't be able to improve the randomness of that very well, and it's 
pretty darn fast... (Though improved versions of those libraries are on 
their way...)

