> o 
> c.s.a.programmer, but anyway...
> 
> Maybe we could between us write some kind of blitz function that gives a
> standard (font sensitive) window for help that everyone agrees looks good.
> I dont know if this would be beneficial to people - at least then everyone 
> has access to a standard Help thang.
> 
> What do people think of this?
> 
> Mark Tiffany

Mark|All,
	 It would be easy to write a helplib but the issue is how it would 
work. I think it would be an idea have the following commands,

	InitHelp UseWindow#,MaxWidth,Clearwhenempty

	DisplayHelp helptext$

Usewindow can just be so it does not get in the way of your own window
allocation, max width, well stop help window obscuring too much, and
clearwhenempty allows you to set wether the window disappears when over
nothing.

helptext$ can use a simple markup language to allow maybe bold/underlined
text.

The main issue is how you decide which button the pointer is over. 
If you specify coordinates relative to each window, then it easy
IF you only want help for those buttons in the ACTIVE window. If you 
want it to display help for WHATEVER is under the pointer wether it is
active or not, well that is a different matter. It is still trivial
if no windows are over lapping, but I am not too sure how you 
find out which out of two windows is nearest to the front.

I shall knock up a demo program this weekend and you can see what you 
think...

Nigel Hughes


From ngh94@aber.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:13 1995
Date: Fri, 19 May 1995 14:22:27 +0100
From: NIGEL HUGHES <ngh94@aber.ac.uk>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: A neat fix for Acid library bugs!


Dear All,
	I have come up with a neat command that enables all those Acid
commands that do not work inside statements and functions (like the
ASLFIlerequest stuff) to, well, work! NB these commands work if they
are in the "root" part of your program.

	Anyone who wants a copy will find it part of the next distribution
of ShapeZ. The commands that i have found that have this problem are,


	ASLFilerequest$
	Window 			with a super bitmap

I'm sure others have found more, well they can now ALL work!

	
	Nigel Hughes


