From sis3149@sis.port.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:13 1995
Date: Fri, 19 May 1995 15:06:52 +0100 (BST)
From: Stephen McNamara <sis3149@sis.port.ac.uk>
To: Blitzlist <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: Standard Help?

I think it'd be nice to have standard systems in use throughout software, 
esp. software geared to blitz basic users.  In our own products (map ed, 
shapez) we are trying to make the presentation and method of doing things 
standard.

Doing a standard help requester/online help system would be a nice way to 
start trying to create a larger picture.  Everyone will have their own 
ideas about what sort of help would be necessary.  Personally I think it 
should be a DOpus 4 type help, where you select the help gadget, then 
click on the gadget/menu item you want help on.  Then a requester opens 
up with the information for that gadget/menu.

Maybe this could be a little compo - we talked about one on the list ages 
ago but nothing every took off.  Now that the list has got some semblance 
of life back into it, it may be a good idea to try something like this...


Later,
Steve Mc.

