Cc: Blitz Basic Mailing List <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: Re: Standard Help?

> Doing a standard help requester/online help system would be a nice way to 
> start trying to create a larger picture.  Everyone will have their own 
> ideas about what sort of help would be necessary.  Personally I think it 
> should be a DOpus 4 type help, where you select the help gadget, then 
> click on the gadget/menu item you want help on.  Then a requester opens 
> up with the information for that gadget/menu.

I like the help system in ReOrg (maybe an old version): You press "Help" (or
select help from a menu) and the mouse pointer turns into a smaller pointer
plus a "?". You now click on a gadget, and a window pops up saying what the
gadget does. To get out of help mode just press "Help" again.

IMHO the best help system I've ever seen. Worked beautifully.

