From phips@scout.rhein-main.deSun Sep  3 22:30:13 1995
Date: Sat, 20 May 95 14:34:42 CET
From: Philipp Lonke <phips@scout.rhein-main.de>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: STANDARD HELP? (fwd)

Hi MO, you wrote in <9505191429.AA06032@sun1.bham.ac.uk> on May 19:

> 	.-------------------------.
> 	|I|_______________________|   <--- Here goes the short desc.
> 	|                         |
> 	|                         |
> 	|                         |   <--- Here goes a longer desc.
> 	|                         |
> 	'-------------------------'

Where the longer desc. should be an option which could be turned
on/off via 
                LongHelp On|Off
So only a short Titlebar pops on, if the user want's it.

> >	InitHelp UseWindow#,MaxWidth,Clearwhenempty
> >
> >	DisplayHelp helptext$
> 
> Something like this is what I had in mind, although commands more like..
> 
> InitHelp UseWindow#,x,y,w,h   <-- sets up help stuff 'forever'
> ClearWhenEmpty On|Off         <-- a flag so it could be turned on/off as needed
> OpenHelp                      <-- open the help window
> CloseHelp                     <-- close the help window
> CurrentHelp simple$,helptext$ <-- (instead of DisplayHelp)

To set the text to a gadget, you should use the following thing:

    HotHelp gadgetlist#,gadget#,shorthelp$,longhelp$

And it should work with BlitzGadgets, GadToolsgadgets, MUI, Triton and
all the other GUIs!!

> 	A markup language would help, but we only need a few things, such as
> bold and underline.  Obviously not neede for simple$ (this is what goes in
> the window title).

I recommend HTML or the Amigaguide-Language. Do not reinvent the wheel
;)

