From relmore@silver.sdsmt.eduSun Sep  3 22:30:13 1995
Date: Sun, 21 May 1995 07:07:05 -0600 (MDT)
From: "Richard T. Elmore" <relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu>
To: Brian Skreeg <oz@ozzy.demon.co.uk>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: ASM tan table (I refuse to give up)

On Fri, 19 May 1995, Brian Skreeg wrote:

> Ok, This is my third plea for assistance concerning my tan table. 
> I refuse to give up on my quest for help simply because I can't figure it 
> out myself and I can go no further without it.
> 	I need to generate a tan table for ASM (most likely in words) with 256
> antries from 0 to 90 degrees. My main problem is I don't know how to create
> the actual file and put my data into it? Help?......please?.

The easiest method I know of is to put the values into an array of words 
and save it out to disk using WriteMem... The following example may or 
may not create the table you have in mind, but it should illustrate how 
you'd save it out and later access it:

;Build Table (Separate Program)
Dim tbl.w(89)
For i=0 to 89:tbl(i)=Tan(i):Next   ;(You'd probably modify this)

If WriteFile(0,"Bin:Tan90.tab")
	WriteMem 0,&tbl(0),(90*SizeOf.w)
EndIf
CloseFile 0



;This is a different program, to illustrate accessing the table again...

;Get the table's value for Tan(45)
v.w=Peek.w(?tantab+45*SizeOf.w)
NPrint v
MouseWait:End

tantab: IncBin "Bin:Tan90.tab"


	+---------------------------------------------------------------+
	|      Richard T. Elmore   -   "Head" of HeadSoft Software      |
	| E-MAIL: relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu          TEL: (605) 348-3337 |     
	+---------------------------------------------------------------+







