From ngh94@aber.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:14 1995
Date: Mon, 22 May 1995 09:09:57 +0100
From: NIGEL HUGHES <ngh94@aber.ac.uk>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Standard Help Library On Line and WORKING!


Dear All,
	I have with me a new version of ShapeZ that uses my new Standard
help library.

	It is in the end, very configurable.

	There are 3 (user setable) levels of help.

	Prompt,
	Hint,
	Reveal.

	Where the help appears is also configurable. If we have a button


      NW   N     NE
	________
	|      |
      SW|      | E
	|      |
	--------
      SW   S     SE

	You can make help appear at anyof the corners. You can ignore
all of these and just set Help to appear in a fixed x,y position. You can
even have a combination where the x,y position is an offset from N,NE,E,SE,S
,SW,W,NW.

	You may also set a delay (number of INTUITICKS) before the help
window appears, this stops it flickering around after you.

	I have a version of ShapeZ with  this feature in (On the control
window and Editor window) which well let you control any of the above
settings.

	I could also have an option for it only to appear when the user
clicks, which would satisfy all those people who wanted that.

	What I would suggest is for me to write a preferences program so 
each user can set Blitz Help to behave how they want it. Every program that
uses help should check the settings in here.

	I will make up a release for everyone as soon as people have seen
it and OK'ed it. I think you will like it a lot.

	There are a few problems with uneven text formatting, but it IS font
sensitive.

	Anyone who made a request for ShapeZ from Friday onwards will get a 
copy sent straight away. Mark you can have one now as well 8)

	Nigel Hughes

