From relmore@silver.sdsmt.eduSun Sep  3 22:30:14 1995
Date: Mon, 22 May 1995 07:29:41 -0600 (MDT)
From: "Richard T. Elmore" <relmore@silver.sdsmt.edu>
To: MO Tiffany <cca93057@sun1.bham.ac.uk>
Cc: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: STANDARD HELP

On Mon, 22 May 1995, MO Tiffany wrote:

> Can we try and put this help code into an actual library, as in a
> 'help.library' file?  Anyone know how to do this, and would this be a good

I was just wondering why nobody is using the amigaguide.library like 
developers in most other languages do... It's part of the OS since 2.04, 
so it's the "standard" for hypertext on the Amiga...

Combined with a "help-mode" for your gadgets and menus, it appears to me 
it would be the best way to handle "help."

In case there are those of you out there who haven't played with 
Amigaguide.library, you can set it up to open it's window on your own 
screen, as well as load datatypes objects in 3.0 and above... It's really 
pretty nice.


