From D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:14 1995
Date: Mon, 22 May 1995 16:13:24 +0100 (BST)
From: Pink <D.C.J.Pink@herts.ac.uk>
To: The Blitz list <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: RE: Making A simple Star Field ?

Just recently Hesham Amiri was asking about how to make a Star Field such 
as that used in the excellent BlitzBlank 2.60, the latest version which 
can be found on Aminet.  Despite the name, most of the blanker modules 
were written in C, and those that are not, such as my Plasma module, 
cannot use Blitz`s own screen/palette/drawing commands, as they are 
currently not compatible with graphics cards.  The BlitzBlank.library 
opens a screen for you automatically, and all drawing/blitting etc. is 
done using OS commands.  If you are familiar with using C then you should 
have no trouble using these OS commands in Blitz as they are identical.  
As for how to create a star field using them, I`ll leave that up to you! :)

If you want a small example of how to interface with BlitzBlank in Blitz2 
then let me know.

