On Sun, 21 May 1995, Josh Farley wrote:

> 
> Hmm... the following section of code produces a "serial port not open" 
> error on line 2...
> 
> a.l=OpenSerial("serial.device",1,19200,128)
> If a<>0 Then SetSerialLens1,8,8,1
> 
> Now, shouldn't OpenSerial return 0 when I try to open Unit 1?  It doesn't...
> 
> Josh
> 
> 
> 
> 


try this...

;---------------------------------begin-----------------------

.openser
If OpenSerial ("serial.device",0,19200,128+32+16+4)=0
   r.b=RTEZRequest("ERROR","Could NOT Open Serial Port!","Damn (QUIT)")
   ser.b=0
   Goto quit
EndIf
SetSerialBuffer 0,16000

;---------------------------------end-------------------------

it works in my program :)
