well, actually I just finished a cool little tool that AUTODIALS my
SLIP account. Its fully definable through the tooltypes...
you set everything including unit#,serial,init command,dial prefix,
name,password...... you set strings to look for like "Password:"
when it gets that it will send whatever you set for the password.

ANYWAY, its cool... it dials, redials..until it connects (if you set it
like that) and the logs you in (sends name/passeord) looks for
a string like SLIP/PPP start at port... (or whatever you set) and then
it quits and (if you set it) starts AmiTCP..... shwooo.

I dunno if this interests anyone. It will be ready any day now. Rich
is trying to help me set a CON: (for the CLI startnet to execute)...

if you could send me some code showing how i can open a con for a cli
program, i would deeply appreciate it :)

Tom.
