From: Gregory Caldwell <greg@redfive.demon.co.uk>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Sound Sampling in BB2

Hi Everyone,

I thought I'd drop a line to ask for a bit of help if possible. I am
intending to write a sound sampling/real time effects prog ib BB2.

The problem I have is that I don't know the best way to capture the
samples. Yes I can read the parallel port and extract sample data but
there is no timing involved and I need to be able to apply a variable
sample rate on the capture.

I presume it has to be done through a timer interrupt of some
description but my other attempts at IRQ's other than a vertical blank
IRQ seem to fail dismally. This goes for capturing serial port info
as well (but that's a different story/program).

Any pointers, help, info, sound sampling progam code or someone who can
tell me the answers to everything would be most appreciated.

Cheers for any response.

Greg


