From cca93057@sun1.bham.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:15 1995
Date: Thu, 25 May 1995 13:20:48 +0100
From: MO Tiffany <cca93057@sun1.bham.ac.uk>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Re: Heir to Jurgen Valks?


Josh Wrote:

> On Thu, 25 May 1995, MO Tiffany wrote:
> 
>> so what i suggest is that other people write their _OWN_ web pages 
>> and then i can link into them directly.  If you want details on how to write 
>> html web pages, contact your sysop/webmaster, and also read through the guide
>> to writing html - There is a link for that on the BPR section of my website.
> 
>   I've never written a web page (I just got AmiTCP and Amosaic to run 
> without crashing)... how do I set one up?  I don't mean writing the html 
> file, I can do that... 

OK.  You can only have a web page (basically) if your web address (URL) is
online all the time.  There need to be programs running that handle the 
accessing of your files, and this is normally handled by someone normally
called the WebMaster.  If you are on a Uni account, then you can probably
set yourself up, otherwise it will be harder - i really dont know what you
would need to do (anyone else know??)

Writing the pages once you have been setup on your system is 'fairly'
easy.  You use a markup language called HTML (theres a guide to it linked 
from my web page), which is 'similar' to amigaguide stuff.  Remember that
in mosaic/netscape there is an option to view the actual html source for
what you are looking at - this is one of the best ways to find out what you
can achieve.

This is an OFFER coming up.....

If anyone CANNOT set up a web page on their own site, then I can provide
storage for it.  If anyone wants to do this, then it is _YOUR_ responsibility
to update it.  All I will do is put it into my disk area and link it into my 
webpage.  You send me new/updated files as and when you want.
THIS IS NOT AN OFFER FOR _ANY_ WEB PAGE.  ONLY BLITZ STUFF PLEASE!!!!

Thank you.

Mark Tiffany

