I suspect you are a raisin in assuming that. :) (I know its currant
not current)

> 
> 
> 	p$="Myprog"
> 	f$="NIL:"
> 	Execute_ (&p$,&f$)`
> 
> 	And if so, why does it not work?

Err...execute takes 3 args

Execute_ p$,<inputfilehandle>,<outputfilehandle>

so it would be Execute_ p$,0,0 (for NIL output)

Steve.
