From josh@pinsight.comSun Sep  3 22:30:15 1995
Date: Thu, 25 May 1995 11:57:10 -0700 (PDT)
From: Josh Farley <josh@pinsight.com>
To: Tom Kruk <tomkruk@escape.com>
Cc: Simon's BLITZ-LIST <blitz-list@helsinki.fi>
Subject: Re: The CONing game...



On Thu, 25 May 1995, Tom Kruk wrote:

> > > I am not all too familiar with fancy dos calls (not many anyway)
> > > and my dialer needs to open a CON window..
> > 
> >   Are you talking about opening up a console?  If so, you need to use a 
> > completely different setup... I can show you how, if that's what you're 
> > 
>    YEAH.. I want to open a CONsole for a program that I am executing.
>    You know how some things need a CON output window. Like in OPUS
>    or Tools Daemon (you set WB or CLI) and if its CLI it opens a CONsole
>    output for that program. 
> 
>    You see I am trying to execute a program startnet (AmiTCP) and it needs
>    an output window!

  I'm not sure opening a console is enough in this instance... you need 
to be able to direct the output...

  I wonder if executing IconX with startnet as an argument would do the 
job...

  Here's my console code, anyway...

  If *conmp=0 Then *conmp=CreateMsgPort_
 If *conmp.MsgPort
  If *conio.IOStdReq=0 Then *conio=CreateIORequest_(*conmp, SizeOf .IOStdReq)
   If *conio
    *conio\io_Data=*mw0.Window
    *conio\io_Length=SizeOf .Window
    cd=OpenDevice_("console.device",0,*conio,0)
    *conu.ConUnit=*conio\io_Unit
   EndIf
  EndIf
 EndIf


*mw0 must be a pointer to a window.

Hope this helps...

