Subject: Delivery failure notification

With reference to your message with the subject:
   "Re: Am I moaning or not?"

One or more addresses in your message have failed with the following
responses from the mail transport system:

   <ZHUNT@Calumet.Yorku.Ca>
   User 'ZHUNT' is not authorised to use mail.

If the problem with your message was an incorrect address for a
recipient at Calumet.YorkU.Ca, you can search for a user at 
Calumet.YorkU.Ca by sending email to:

   maiser@calumet.yorku.ca 

with the following as the body of the message

    LOOKUP <string>
       - Returns a list of users at this address who match
         the string you supply. The string may contain * and
         ? wildcard characters. Do NOT include the < > in your 
         LOOKUP request.
         <string> should be the persons userid only.  For example
         to search for Pat Rogers, your message might include the
         following:

         lookup *pat*
         lookup *rog*

         Do _NOT_ use eMail addresses in lookup commands
         (ie: don't do a - lookup progers@calumet.yorku.ca)
        

If the above error is a "File creation error delivering to 'recipient'"
it is possible that the recipient has exceeded their email disk quota.
If this is the cause of the error, the recipient will not be able
to receive any email until they free up some space by deleting 
some of their email.


If you require assistance, please mail postmaster@CALUMET.YORKU.CA.

                Virtually Yours,
                     The Calumet Postmaster

