From mca@glasgow-caledonian.ac.ukSun Sep  3 22:30:16 1995
Date: Tue, 30 May 1995 12:39:53 +0300
From: "M.Carter" <mca@glasgow-caledonian.ac.uk>
To: blitz-list@helsinki.fi
Subject: Arexx in Blitz Basic

AREXX IN BLITZ BASIC
====================

Has anyone managed to get ARexx to work in Blitz Basic? On
an old BUM disk (you could argue that ALL the disks are old -
it's been such a long time since anyone received the last
one), there were a set of ARexx examples - bpaint.bb,
roger2.rexx, etc. ...

I cannot get them to work. They compile and run, but none of
the commands added works. The .rexx scripts do not return. 

I can affirm that the following has been done :
   - REXXMAST process activated
   - BPAINT program executed before rexx script activated.

I have a book called 'Arexx: Your Amiga's Built-in Turbocharger'.
They give C code of how to implement an Arexx port. The sequence
of processing looks nothing like that given in the Blitz Programs.
I have a feeling that that might be the problem.

The BB2 function GetRexxCommand() cpaitalises the command argument.
How do I arrange it so that it doesn't do that? Also, why is it that
rm_Args(1) isn't a string? How do I get a string from it - and will
it preserve the case of the command argument?


POINTERS
========

Blitz Basic 2 has a way of dealing with pointers which seems
different from C.

Type in the following program :
   NEWTYPE.mytype
      a.l
      *letters.s
   End NEWTYPE

   DEFTYPE.mytype struct, *ptr

   *ptr=&struct  ;see comment below

   struct\letters="how now brown cow"
   NPrint struct\letters
   *ptr\letters="and silly sow"
   NPrint struct\letters

   MouseWait
   End

Output is :
   how now brown cow
   and silly sow

By rights, the line *ptr=&struct is wrong. ptr is a pointer
t0 mytype, so it really ought to be
   ptr=&struct   (without the asterix)

BB2 only seems to give one type of dereferencing. Hmm... it
works, but C seems to have a uniformity of meaning that BB2
doesn't. Maybe someone could give us a tutorial on the BUM to
explain, conceptually, how BB2 interprets pointers.


-------------------------------------
To   : blitz-list@helsinki.fi
>From : mca@uk.ac.gcal (Mark Carter)
Date : 28 May 1995
File : arexx.bb



