Subject: Re: C=

Hello,

> does anybody know the current state of Commodore i.e.. is the 060

Commodore is selled to Escom. A 060-Amiga would be a surprise but it
is not impossible. Nothing is impossible at the moment. :-)
The first date for continuing the Amiga-line is September, but this is
neither sure nor definitive. They will continue the C64, A1200, A4000
(possibly with new case). The C64 is planned for the East- and China-
market. I'm not sure, if the A600 will also continue, but i have heard
something like that...

> amiga going to be made, what about the RISC based amiga`s ?

Nobody knows if it will be a HP-PA or PowerPC-based Amiga. Also not
Escom! They rethink yet, which processor is the better solution for the
future. Any other report of "definitive PowerPC-based" is a rumour.
But a RISC-based Amiga will come...

> is there still a future for Commodore...

Possibly not for Commodore Amiga, but the Amiga from Amiga
Technologies GmbH has a future. :-)

> any info at all would be help, our a pointer in the right dirwction
> to find this info 

Well, look out in the comp.sys.amiga.advocacy and -misc newsgroups for
messages from Dr. P. Kittel. He is the new head of Engineering for the
Amiga.

bye

Andrew



