Hiho Studer,

> Hello,
> 
> > does anybody know the current state of Commodore i.e.. is the 060
> 
> Commodore is selled to Escom. A 060-Amiga would be a surprise but it
> is not impossible. Nothing is impossible at the moment. :-)
> The first date for continuing the Amiga-line is September, but this is
> neither sure nor definitive. They will continue the C64, A1200, A4000
> (possibly with new case). The C64 is planned for the East- and China-
> market. I'm not sure, if the A600 will also continue, but i have heard
> something like that...

At the ESCOM press conference on the 30th they said that 25000 A4000
are slated of production in September. 10000 would be 060 with a licsenced
Cyberstorm (phase5) card inside and 15000 plain 040. They also have said
they plan to sell 12000-13000 A1200 this year alone (these will be made in
september also). No prices were stated. They have also setup R&D in the
ol Norristown site and in Germany and are working very closely with SCALA
and Motorolla so a PPC amiga looks likely even though they said they hadn't
made a decsision on which processor to use. Amiga Development is
continuing. YEEEHHAAAA!
	They also said SCALA MM300 will be packaged with all Amigas including
A1200's. Look's like they're really pushing the miggie into the
serious/multimedia market.


